TestHandledFlagFalseWhenRecoveryFails
/ When the recovery body itself throws, error.handle.Wrap leaves Handled=false on the inner Call and re-throws — the original error propagates (with the recovery error chained) and the outer handler catches it. Side-effect proof: %outerCaught% gets set by the outer handler, which only fires if the inner recovery failed and re-threw.
- call InnerWithFailingRecovery, on error set %outerCaught% = true
- assert %outerCaught% is true, "outer handler should have caught — recovery body must have re-thrown"

InnerWithFailingRecovery
/ Throws "boom", whose recovery body itself throws "recovery-failed". The outer-most on-error in the test goal is the only one that can catch.
- throw error "boom", on error throw error "recovery-failed"
